      "span_text": "Since synapses containing homomeric α3 GlyRs are weakly expressed in the mature vertebrate brain, it is possible that the switch we detected in the expression levels of GLRA2 and GLRA3 reflects a shift from homomeric α2 GlyRs to heteromeric α3β GlyRs, similar to the switch reported from α2 to α1β in rats."
